Anonymous Sat 14 Sep 2019 00:28:55 No.25405625 Report
Quoted By:
>>25405506
Exactly. You can build the list as you go along so long as you keep an eye on what the reader can learn about the characters.
I intentionally started giving grades and titles to characters in the story I mentioned with two main species. So colours (the scarlet x) and ranks (the sergeant) merging with attributes (the firmly built), history (the tortured) and acts or behaviors (the vicious) all start giving you a load of ways to refer to a character with absolutely no use of their name and the reader can still keep up.
It's a damn good thing to make use of. Literally the writing giving you back tools to deepen the story in return.
